  "text": "It is worth pointing out that in our case the quadratic functional I(v) : = a(v, v)=2 À '(v) represents the strain energy of the system [CITATION_1] . At this point the reader has noticed that the last condition needed for the successful application of Lax-Milgram's lemma, that is the boundedness of the linear functional ', is left unchecked, thus, voiding the proof by Altan [CITATION_2] . Is this functional continuous on V A ? The answer to this question is: it depends on the kernel A. Let us elaborate on this answer with the following discussion.",
